###  https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerTransmissionProcess
copi:PowerTransmissionProcess rdf:type owl:Class ;
                              rdfs:label "power transmission process"@en ,
                                         "processo de transmissão de potência"@pt-br ;
                              annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transferred from a prime mover through a rotating shaft to one or more driven machines, typically involving the conversion of torque and rotational speed to match operational requirements."@en ,
                                                                   "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted from a driving component to a driven component through the rotation or linear motion of a shaft, enabling the transfer of torque and rotational speed."@en ,
                                                                   "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted from an external energy source through a rotating shaft to downstream mechanical components, enabling power transfer within a mechanical system."@en ,
                                                                   "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical energy is transmitted through rotational motion from one component to another via a rotating shaft, enabling the transfer of torque and angular velocity to mounted components."@en ,
                                                                   "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical power is transferred from one rotating or reciprocating component to another through direct mechanical engagement, resulting in motion transmission and potentially torque or speed modification."@en ,
                                                                   "A PlannedProcess in which mechanical rotational energy is transmitted from a prime mover through a shaft to driven components, resulting in the transfer of torque and rotational motion necessary for equipment operation."@en .


